	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok.. Here we go.. I know it's been mentioned, but I will go through it anyway.<BR>
<BR>
First, as far as the heart being more rare? Thta is incorrect. After 3 weeks of ona nd off camping Grimrot, I got 3 undead spawns within 3 days. Sadly noone was around to claim loot on the other 2.<BR>
Now here is the basic idea to the camp.<BR>
<BR>
Apparently live Lord Grimrot has an 8 hour spawn, so be prepared to spend some time watching. You will see many place holders. Basically what you want to do is sit and watch. Grimrot in both forms spawns under the platform that is missing a lamp on top in the northeast corner of the ruins. Ghanex Drah spawns in the southeast corner (he's not the PH). Ghanex is involved in a seperate Monk quest.<BR>
The spawn time of the ph's if killed is 3 hours and 15 minutes, or thereabouts. I have waited as long as 4 hours for one to spawn.<BR>
I have heard rumors of killing the ph to time spawn him as a day spawn for live, which is correct, but you almost have to keep it going for 8 hours, or hope most of that time has already lapsed before you took the camp. But you can also let the ph stay up, and let it despawn. But if you do this, protect it. Aviaks that are low enough to be a battle for the putrid skeletons that litter the ruins will attack them, and I have lost a ph a few times to them and gotten a wrongly times spawn. IE. night spawn, for an undead Grimrot.<BR>
Eventually Live Grimrot will spawn. And yes, he's approximately lvl 35, and has a harm touch which will take about 400 hits. If you wait long enough to kill him, he'll make a pet. Kill him right away. Doing this will also make sure the next spawn will occur at night.<BR>
Bear in mind, undead Grimrot may not spawn after the first 3 hours and 15 minutes. But when he does spawn, he'll make a pet. Undead Grimrot is around lvl 25 or so. His pet is easy, but for me at lvl 50 was an easy kill. For the Clerics of Norrath, bring a melee friend to help you. You'll need him. Even if you are level 50.<BR>
Paladins will have the easiest time gaining faction with the Temple of Life. This is because for those that have done the armor of ro quests, had to gain high enough faction to get the mold for the vambraces in rathe mountains. But the faction needed is as high as you can get to get the Aegis of Life from Camlend.<BR>
Bandit sashes is the easiest way to raise faction, and bring a lot of them. Hit the bank if you have to and empty out your bags except for neccessities, and go find the bandits of WK and get as many as you can. Like was mentioned keep turning them in until the only faction you get from them is with the Temple of Life. At that point you should be able to turn the items in.<BR>
As far as racial abilities to get the shield? They don't exist. Only faction will stop you. I am a Half Elf Paladin, and know others, plus Dwarf Paladins and Clerics that have been successful in the quest.<BR>
It's not a difficult quest, just time consuming. So go to the video store, rent a few movies and get your favorite snacks, cause there's going to be a wait.<BR>
After camping Lord Grimrot for a month (on and off) I compiled this info for you all.<BR>
Good luck and have fun.<BR>
<BR>
Carnath Angelknight<BR>
Paladin of Tunare 50th season<BR>
The Rathe
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
